discussion.p:
Consider the following case:



template <typename T> constexpr bool P = true;
constexpr bool Q = true;

template <typename T = int> requires P<T>
void foo(int = 0, T = 0);

template <typename U = int> requires P<U> && Q
void foo(U = 0, int = 0);

void bar() { foo(); }



It seems that <T> in the first declaration of
foo() may be considered equivalent to P<U> in
the second declaration of foo(); however, I would find it surprising if the call
to foo() is unambiguous. Note that T and U
are not involved in the partial ordering in this case aside from the determination
of the more constrained template.
